  "text": "A Geographical Information System (GIS) is a software system that provides the functionality to develop, maintain, analyze and handle geo-spatial information [CITATION_1] ]. These systems are mainly developed in a multilayered style, so that various forms of information can be integrated into a single model. The three most important features of a geographical information system that makes it appealing to the study of infrastructure systems are:",
